  "prompt": "Does it hurt to get stitches removed?",
  "response": "Removing stitches typically does not hurt, though you might feel some discomfort or a mild prick when the stitches are being taken out. Most people describe the sensation as similar to having a small tug or pull on the skin. If the stitches are removed after the appropriate healing time, the area should be less sensitive. However, if the stitches are removed too early or if the wound is not healing properly, you may experience more discomfort. It's always best to talk to your healthcare provider if you're concerned about pain during the removal process.",
